==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒt|-ɒt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A broad, flat, wooden bar; a slat or sloat.
#A bolt or bar for fastening a door. ([[Prov. Eng.]]).
#A narrow depression, perforation, or aperture; especially, one for the reception of a piece fitting or sliding in it.
#The allocated time for an aircraft's departure or arrival at an airport's runway.
#The track of a deer; hence, a track of any kind. ([[w:Milton]])
#:Quotation: As a bloodhound follows the slot of a hurt deer. --[[w:Sir W. Scott]]
#In a flying display, the forth position; after the leader and two wingmen.
